  "body": "Issue to manage mobile release 1.15.0\r\n\r\n### Scope\r\n[comment]: # (Add milestone from github)\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-react/milestone/54\r\n\r\n- release notes: https://notes.status.im/s/3KPug1hkK\r\n- release branch: https://github.com/status-im/status-react/tree/release/1.15.x\r\n\r\n\r\n### Testing info \r\n[comment]: # (TestRail info, added by QA)\r\nMain test suite: https://ethstatus.testrail.net/index.php?/runs/view/7596&group_by=cases:section_id&group_order=asc&group_id=890\r\nUpgrade (e2e): none; upgrade will be tested manually this time, as navigation changed\r\n\r\n### Builds in TestFlight and PlayStore to push as a release\r\n[comment]: # (Will be added by QA after testing approving of build)\r\nAPK: https://status-im-releases.ams3.digitaloceanspaces.com/StatusIm-Mobile-v1.15.0-81a206-universal.apk\r\nIOS: 1.15.0(20210712120616)\r\n\r\n### Process\r\n#### 1) Kick-off\r\n- [x] 1. Translation PRs is merged before cutting branch (Jinho)\r\n- [x] 2. Prepare scope of visible changes based on commits history, started from previous release branch cut ([example]( https://notes.status.im/1.14-release-notes?view))\r\n- [x] 3. Update [RELEASES.md](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/blob/develop/RELEASES.md) with release notes (make PR based on previous step)\r\n- [x] 4. Create 1.14.0 release branch and get successful builds (doc is [here](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/blob/develop/doc/RELEASE_GUIDE.md) so, testing can be started)\r\n- [x] 5. Based on release scope, ask for comms (Jonny) \r\n- [x] 6. Make sure that assets (screenshots, video) in stores are up to date. If should be updated, ask @cammellos  for help\r\n\r\n#### 2) Testing\r\n[comment]: # (Section will be maintained by QA)\r\n- [x] Dogfooding [(notes)](https://notes.status.im/DoYCPsVbRmurpmznmNVbCQ?edit) \r\n- [x] Regression testing for release candidate build\r\n- [x] Upgrade tests\r\n- [x] Fix known blocker(s) found during regression testing\r\n\r\n##### Blockers\r\n[comment]: # (Section for blocker issues; should be fixed and merged by release-manager. Remove if no blockers found)\r\n- [x] 1 blocker: https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/12294\r\n- [x] 2 blocker: https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/12297\r\n- [x] 3 blocker: https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/12296\r\n- [x] 4 blocker: https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/12302\r\n\r\n=============================================================================================\r\n\r\n- [x] Cherry-pick fix(es) to the release branch\r\n- [x] Verify fix(es) on new release candidate build\r\n- [x] Retest\r\n- [x] Keep release build forever (button in Jenkins)\r\n\r\n#### 3) Submission\r\n\r\n- [x] 1. Release notes written and added (500 character limit for updates (Android) and PR for [RELEASES.md](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/blob/develop/RELEASES.md) is ready to be merged (from 1.3 step)\r\n- [x] 2. Submit beta version for Android (Open Testing in Play Store)\r\n- [x] 3. Submit iOS build to Apple review ([instruction](https://drive.google.com/file/d/10Cl7PBB7TFPkZiVbfzdFGpfMRP9bxXuq/view?usp=sharing), be careful - low quality of audio)\r\n- [x] 4. Play store content reviewed and updated\r\n- [x] 5. Privacy policy reviewed and updated (ask in channel)\r\n- [x] 6. Countries to be excluded (ask in channel) \r\n- [x] 7. Changes to our FAQ made (should be checked and if any changes needed, ask Jakub to made them)\r\n- [x] 8. Prepare PR for F-droid build ([instruction]( https://github.com/status-im/status-react/blob/develop/doc/FDROID.md))\r\n\r\n#### 4) Before publishing\r\n- [x] 1. Translations for comms available (marketing, ask in the channel)\r\n- [x] 2. Promotional content ready (marketing, ask in channel)\r\n- [x] 3. Upload builds for DO store,  https://dev.status.im/ (Jakub)\r\n\r\n#### 5) At time of publishing\r\n- [x] 1. Notify marketing to push comms and blog post (Jonny)\r\n- [x] 2. Publish release to app store and playstore\r\n- [x] 3. Final push to update prod site https://status.im/,  [instructions](https://github.com/status-im/infra-docs/blob/master/articles/status_release_upload.md) (Jakub - requires credentials to upload) \r\n- [x] 4. Add the link to the post about the release and publish the release: https://github.com/status-im/status-react/releases (Jakub)\r\n- [x] 5. Merge PR for updating [RELEASES.md](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/blob/develop/RELEASES.md) (from 1.3 step)\r\n\r\n",
